#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -u

ROOT_DIR="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")/.." && pwd)"
# shellcheck source=../config/env
source "$ROOT_DIR/config/env"

cat <<'EOF'
MIDI route examples only. Nothing is executed by this script.

ALSA aconnect direction is:

  aconnect SOURCE DESTINATION

Recommended topology:

  Bome OUT -> VirMIDI -> Ableton IN

Example routes:

  aconnect "VirMIDI 1-0:0" "WINE midi driver:0"
  aconnect "WINE midi driver:0" "VirMIDI 1-0:0"

Directionality:

  "VirMIDI 1-0:0" -> "WINE midi driver:0"
    Sends MIDI arriving at the VirMIDI port into Wine/Ableton.

  "WINE midi driver:0" -> "VirMIDI 1-0:0"
    Sends MIDI emitted by Wine/Ableton back toward the VirMIDI port.

Actual ALSA client names and numeric IDs vary by boot, module load order,
Wine process, and session state. Run:

  ./bin/midi-route-inspect

Then use the exact client/port names or client:port IDs shown on this machine.
EOF
